<br>
Gotta agree on NTOV.  It's the only raid zone I know where you always see so many happy people at the end of the night.  Always tons of excitement over drops there.  The fights are fun, too.  NTOV is to raid zones what L.Guk was to xp zones back in pre-kunark days (or Seb for you younguns).  Very nicely balanced risk/reward there.<br>
<br>
Sad thing is, most people won't be able to experience it.  The only folks that really get to have fun doing NTOV/ST/etc. are those in the guild that gets there first and that's typically only for a few months.  After that, the crowding makes it a real pain.  I hope POP has some fun zones with good rewards and that those zones are done with the zone-copy method I've been hearing about.  It would be nice if everyone could someday enjoy crawling through an unspoiled zone without having to deal with all the competition drama. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

